Description:
AWARD PURPOSE
THIS GRANT WILL PROVIDE FINANCIAL RESOURCES TO ENABLE THE KANSAS DEPARTMENT OF COMMERCE (KDOC) TO CONTINUE TASKS NECESSARY TO DEVELOP, AND SUBSEQUENTLY MAINTAIN A FEDERAL EMPLOYMENT DATA EXCHANGE SYSTEM (FED ES). THE FEDES IS A COMPREHENSIVE DATA EXCHANGE SYSTEM THAT WILL PROVIDE FEDERAL AND MILITARY EMPLOYMENT WAGE DATA TO GRANTEES OF THE U.S. DEPARTMENT OF LABOR 
(USDOL), EMPLOYMENT AND TRAINING ADMINISTRATION (ETA). THESE DATA ARE NOT AVAILABLE THROUGH THE STATE WAGE INTERCHANGE SYSTEM (SWIS) AND OBTAINING FEDERAL AND MILITARY EMPLOYMENT DATA WILL PROVIDE A MORE COMPLETE PICTURE OF A GRANTEE'S PERFORMANCE, PARTICULARLY IN GEOGRAPHIC LOCATIONS WITH HIGH CONCENTRATION OF FEDERAL AND MILITARY EMPLOYMENT, WHICH ENHANCES THE DATA THAT GRANTEES PROVIDE FOR STATUTORILY REQUIRED REPORTING. THE OVERALL DESIGN IS INTENDED TO SUPPORT THE QUARTERLY EXCHANGE OF DATA BETWEEN ALL 50 STATES OF THE UNITED STATES, AS WELL AS THE DISTRICT OF COLUMBIA, PUERTO RICO, AND THE UNITED STATES VIRGIN ISLANDS. 

ACTIVITIES PERFORMED
THE ACTIVITY TO BE FUNDED IS ESSENTIAL TO THE SATISFACTORY COMPLETION OF AN ACTIVITY PRESENTLY FUNDED BY DOL, WHEREIN COMPETITION WOULD RESULT IN SIGNIFICANT OR REAL: EXPENSES IN EXCESS OF ANY POTENTIAL SAVINGS TO THE GOVERNMENT; DISRUPTION TO PROGRAM SERVICES; DUPLICATION OF WORK AT ADDITIONAL COST TO THE GOVERNMENT; AND SUBSTANTIAL DELAY IN THE TIME OF PROJECT IMPLEMENTATION AND DELIVERABLES.

DELIVERABLES
IN ORDER TO ACCOMPLISH THE STATED PURPOSE OF THIS GRANT AND FACILITATE ACCESS TO FEDERAL WAGE RECORDS IN THE MOST COST EFFECTIVE AND EFFICIENT MANNER, THE TASKS TO BE PERFORMED BY KDOC WILL INCLUDE (BUT ARE NOT LIMITED TO) THE FOLLOWING: •	DESIGN, ESTABLISH, AND MAINTAIN A DATA EXCHANGE INFRASTRUCTURE THAT WILL SUPPORT THE COLLECTION, TRANSMISSION, AND STORAGE OF ET A PROGRAM PARTICIPANTS AND WAGE RECORD INFORMATION OBTAINED FROM THE PARTICIPATING FEDERAL PARTNERS TO STATE AGENCIES, GRANTEES, AND ANY OTHER AUTHORIZED ENTITY;
•	CONSOLIDATE AND TRANSMIT WAGE RECORD REQUESTS ON A QUARTERLY BASIS;
•	PROVIDE FOR AND OVERSEE THE ADMINISTRATION AND OPERATION OFFEDES; IN COLLABORATION WITH ETA AND THE APPLICABLE FEDERAL AGENCIES DEVELOP ALL TECHNICAL DOCUMENTATION THAT WILL PROVIDE DETAILED SPECIFICATIONS REGARDING HOW THE EXCHANGE OF CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION WILL BE CONDUCTED;
•	COORDINATE AND COLLABORATE WITH ETA IN THE DEVELOPMENT OF ANY NECESSARY MEMORANDA OF UNDERSTANDING, AND ANY OTHER REQUIRED AGREEMENTS;
•	COORDINATE AND WORK COLLABORATIVELY WITH THE APPLICABLE FEDERAL AGENCIES AND ETA ON AMENDING AGREEMENTS WITH STATES TO COMPORT WITH STATUTORY AND REGULATORY DEVELOPMENTS;
•	BEFORE SHARING DATA WITH ANY STATE, ENSURING THAT THE STATE HAS A CURRENT MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING (MOU) AND ANY OTHER NECESSARY FORMS AND AGREEMENTS IN PLACE FOR PARTICIPATION IN FEDES;
•	PROVIDE DIRECT TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE (E.G., SUPPORT, TROUBLESHOOTING) TO PARTICIPATING STATE OR FEDERAL AGENCIES IN ESTABLISHING AND TESTING CONNECTIONS TO THE FEDES SYSTEM; NOT TO INCLUDE SUPPORT OF OPERATING SYSTEMS OR AGENCY HARDWARE OR BASIC COMPUTING TRAINING;
•	MAINTAIN A CURRENT LIST, UPDATED QUARTERLY, OF THE STATES PARTICIPATING IN FEDES;
•	DEVELOP AND IMPLEMENT POLICIES AND PROCESSES FOR MATCHING ETA PROGRAM PARTICIPANT DATA WITH THE INFORMATION OBTAINED THROUGH FEDES, IN ACCORDANCE WITH SPECIFICATIONS DEVELOPED IN COLLABORATION WITH AND APPROVED BY ETA;
•	ENSURE THAT ITS PROGRAMMING AND FORMS ARE COMPATIBLE WITH THE CURRENT WIOA REPORTING SYSTEM, AND ANY SUCCESSOR SYSTEMS, AND RECORD LAYOUTS; ENSURE THAT INFORMATION AND DATA WILL BE MAINTAINED AND DISCLOSED IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE REQUIREMENTS OF THE APPLICABLE FEDERAL AGENCIES CONSIST WITH THE AGREEMENTS EXECUTED WITH THE APPLICABLE FEDERAL PARTNER;
MAINTAIN A POLICY OF DATA BREACH INCIDENTS IN ACCORDANCE WITH FEDERAL STATUTE AND REGULATIONS ANDCOMPLY WITH USDOL AND THE APPLICABLE FEDERAL AGENCIES' ESTABLISHED POLICIES AND PROTOCOLS FOR DATA BREACH
•	ALLOW ETA, OR ITS AUTHORIZED REPRESENTATIVE, TO PERFORM PERIODIC ON-SITE INSPECTIONS OR REVIEWS TO ENSURE COMPLIANCE WITH CONFIDENTIALITY RULES AND OTHER PROCEDURES TO SAFEGUARD PERSONALLY IDENTIFIABLE DATA AND ANY OTHER DERIVATIVE FILES, RECORDS, OR REPORTS THAT CONTAIN PERSONALLY IDENTIFIABLE DATA;
•	SECURE AND MAINTAIN AUTHORITY TO OPERATE BY GOING THROUGH THE APPROPRIATE CERTIFICATION AND ACCREDITATION PROCESS, AND PROVIDE A LETTER SIGNED OFF BY SOMEONE WITH THE AUTHORITY TO ACCEPT RESPONSIBILITY AND OBLIGATION FOR THE AGENCY; AND
•	CONDUCT OTHER GRANT ADMINISTRATION ACTIVITIES AS NEEDED.


INTENDED BENEFICIARY
THIS DATA EXCHANGE CAPABILITY IS NEEDED TO PROVIDE STATES, OTHER ETA GRANTEES, AND FEDERAL AGENCIES AN EFFICIENT WAY TO INCLUDE EMPLOYMENT INFORMATION FOR FEDERAL EMPLOYEES IN SUPPORT OF WORKFORCE PERFORMANCE REPORTING, RESEARCH, AND EVALUATION REQUIRED BY WIOA, THE WAGNER-PEYSER ACT, AND OTHER FEDERAL PROGRAMS MANAGED BY ETA PURSUANT TO FEDERAL LAW OR REGULATION. FURTHERMORE, KDOC OPERATES COMMON REPORTING INFORMATION SERVICES (CRIS), WHICH IS A FORMAL PARTNERSHIP WITH KDOC TO MANAGE REQUESTS FOR AGGREGATE WAGE RECORD DATA, AVAILABLE THROUGH SWIS ON BEHALF OF THE ETA NATIONAL AND DISCRETIONARY GRANT PROGRAMS; AND IS BEST POSITIONED TO DEVELOP THE WAGE INTERCHANGE SYSTEM REQUIRED FOR FEDES. 

